JOHANNESBURG - Three-year-old Michael Johnston died while he and his parents were trying to flee the Knysna fires on Wednesday.It was his birthday.His parents, Madre and Tony Johnston, also perished in the blaze.Lunice Johnston, a relative, said Michael was such "a lovely happy little boy ... I suppose that Madre would have baked a cake and made a party for him that this tragic sad event would have unfolded."*Watch the video above for the full interview with Johnston.eNCA